<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-07-10T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-07-10T16:00:00-05:00" n="214" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d214">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72119/1776</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    to the Minister in Switzerland</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_SPA1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Stovall</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-07-10T17:00:00-04:00">
                                        <hi rend="italic">July 10, 1918, 5 p.m.</hi>
                                    </date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>2265. Your 3884, July 5, 9 p.m. It seems obvious that the German
                                peace plan is to sacrifice in the west in order to obtain a vast
                                incalculable gain in the east. <persName>Herron</persName>’s
                                attention might be called to the fact that the Eastern Question is
                                not dealt with in the Bavarian tentative peace program and told that
                                a discussion of a settlement which did not put all the Russian,
                                Turkish, and Eastern cards on the table was not even remotely
                                possible.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName corresp="#p_LR1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>